TY  - JOUR
TI  - Alternative Approaches to the Theory of Choice in Risk-Taking Situations
AU  - Arrow, Kenneth J.
AB  - [This paper seeks to survey the literature in economics, philosophy, mathematics, and statistics on the subject of choice among alternatives the consequences of which are not certain. Attention is centered on the suggested modes of describing uncertainty and on the theories of rational and actual behavior of in individuals making choices.]
